Assignment 14: Twitters Mining with rtweet

How to do it?:

  • Open the Rmarkdown file of this assignment (link) in Rstudio.

  • Right under each question, insert a code chunk (you can use the hotkey Ctrl + Alt + I to add a code chunk) and code the solution for the question.

  • Knit the rmarkdown file (hotkey: Ctrl + Alt + K) to export an html.

  • Publish the html file to your Githiub Page.

Submission: Submit the link on Github of the assignment to Canvas

ts_plot(df, "hours") +
  labs(x = NULL, y = NULL,
       title = "Frequency of Tweets by Time",
       subtitle = paste0(format(min(df$created_at), "%d %B %Y"), " to ", format(max(df$created_at),"%d %B %Y")),
       caption = "The frequency of tweets flucuates over the period including a huge spike around November 22.") +
  theme_minimal()

df %>% 
  unnest_tokens(mentions, text, "tweets", to_lower = FALSE) %>%
  filter(str_detect(mentions, "^@")) %>%  
  count(mentions, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = reorder(mentions, n)))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(x = 'Number of mentions', y = 'Account Mentioned', title = 'Top 10 Mentions Within the Tweets', caption='NHLBruins is the account that is mentioned the most within all of the tweets.')

library(RColorBrewer)

pal <- brewer.pal(8,"Dark2")
library(wordcloud) 
## Warning: package 'wordcloud' was built under R version 4.2.2
df %>% 
  filter(created_at>='2022-11-28') %>% 
  unnest_tokens(output = hashtag, input = text, token = "tweets") %>%
  filter(!hashtag %in% c("#lose"), str_detect(hashtag, "^#")) %>% 
  count(hashtag, sort = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(hashtag = str_remove(hashtag, '#')) %>% 
  filter(hashtag != 'mufc') %>% 
  with(wordcloud(hashtag, n, random.order = FALSE, max.words = 50, colors = pal))

df %>% 
  filter(created_at>='2022-11-28') %>% 
  unnest_tokens(output = hashtag, input = text, token = "tweets") %>%
  filter(!hashtag %in% c("#lose"), str_detect(hashtag, "^#")) %>% 
  count(hashtag, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = reorder(hashtag, n)))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(x = 'Frequency', y = 'Hashtag', title = 'Top 10 Hashtags Within the Tweets', caption = 'bruins, nhl, boston, top25, and nhlbruins are the most common.')

df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = retweet_count, y = favorite_count))+
  geom_point()+
  labs(x = 'Number of Retweets', y = 'Number of Favorites', title = 'Number of Favorites vs Retweets', caption='The general trend is that if a tweet has more retweets, it has more favorites.')

df %>%
    unnest_tokens(input = text, output = word) %>% 
    anti_join(get_stopwords()) %>% 
    count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
    inner_join(get_sentiments("nrc")) %>%
    filter(!is.na(sentiment)) %>%
    count(sentiment, sort = TRUE) %>% 
    mutate(n = n/sum(n)) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(y= reorder(sentiment, n), x = n))+geom_col()+
    labs(y='Relative Frequency', x ='', title='Sentiment of the Tweets', caption ='The tweets have more of a postive sentiment than a negative one.')
